==English==

===Noun===
# Alternate form of "[[three-on-the-tree]]."
# {{idiom}} On an automobile (esp. those produced from 1939 through the mid-1970s), a three-speed manual [[transmission]] whose [[gearshift]] lever is [[mount]]ed on the [[steering column]].
#: ''Mother and Father learned to drive in a car with a '''3-on-the-tree'''.''

===Adjective===
# {{idiom}} On an automobile, describing the gearshift lever of a steering column-mounted three-speed manual transmission.